text: Introduction .

text: Personal experiences of discrimination and bias have been the focus of much social science research . [ 1 - 3 ]

label: nsubj aux root det amod obj nsubj acl amod cc conj obj punct dep punct punct

text: neuroscientists have examined the neurobiological underpinnings of discrimination [ 7 – 9 ] ;
label: nsubj aux root det amod obj case nmod punct dep case nmod punct punct

text: and evolutionary theorists have explored the various ways that in - group / out - group biases emerged across the history of our species . [ 10 ]
label: cc amod nsubj aux root det amod obj mark compound punct compound cc compound punct conj nsubj acl case det obl case nmod nmod punct punct dep punct

text: In many respects , researchers already possess a wealth of knowledge concerning the origins and consequences of discrimination and bias . [ 11 ]

text: What also should not be lost in discussion of discrimination is the growing push to implement social policy aimed at reducing the occurrence of discriminatory practices .

text: At least one prior study by Kessler and colleagues [ 15 ] , however , using measures of perceived discrimination in a large American sample , reported that approximately 33 % of respondents reported some form of discrimination ( see also , Gibbons et al. [ 4 ] ) .

label: case det obl punct det nsubj acl case obl flat root obj case det compound amod obl punct mark det compound nsubj case nmod advcl case det obl case det nmod flat flat cc compound compound conj punct

text: Antonín Dvořák
label: root flat

text: Antonín Leopold Dvořák ( / d(ə)ˈvɔːrʒɑːk , -ʒæk / d(ə)-VOR-zha(h)k ; Czech : [ ˈantoɲiːn ˈlɛopolt ˈdvor̝aːk ] ; 8 September 1841 – 1 May 1904 ) was a Czech composer .
label: nsubj flat flat punct punct appos punct conj punct appos punct dep punct punct parataxis flat flat punct punct nmod compound nmod case nmod compound nmod punct cop det amod root punct

text: After Bedřich Smetana , he was the next Czech Romantic - era composer to achieve worldwide recognition .
label: case nmod flat punct nsubj cop det amod amod amod punct compound root mark acl amod obj punct

text: Following Smetana 's nationalist example , Dvořák frequently employed aspects , specifically rhythms , of the folk music of Moravia and his native Bohemia .
label: case nmod case amod obl punct nsubj advmod root obj punct advmod appos punct case det compound nmod case nmod cc nmod amod conj punct

text: Dvořák 's own style has been described as " the fullest recreation of a national idiom with that of the symphonic tradition , absorbing folk influences and finding effective ways of using them " . [ 1 ]
label: nmod case amod nsubj aux aux root case punct det amod obl case det amod nmod case nmod case det amod nmod punct acl compound obj cc conj amod obj mark acl obj punct punct punct dep punct

text: Antonín Dvořák
label: root flat

text: Dvořák displayed his musical gifts at an early age , being an apt violin student from age six .
label: nsubj root nmod amod obj case det amod obl punct cop det amod compound advcl case nmod nummod punct

text: The first public performances of his works were in Prague in 1872 and , with special success , in 1873 , when he was aged 31 .
label: det amod amod nsubj case nmod nmod cop case root case obl cc punct case amod nmod punct case conj punct advmod nsubj cop advcl xcomp punct

text: Seeking recognition beyond the Prague area , he submitted a score of his First Symphony to a prize competition in Germany , but did not win , and the unreturned manuscript was lost until rediscovered many decades later .
label: advcl obj case det compound obl punct nsubj root det obj case nmod amod nmod case det compound obl case nmod punct cc aux advmod conj punct cc det amod nsubj aux conj mark advcl amod obl advmod punct

text: In 1874 he made a submission to the Austrian State Prize for Composition , including scores of two further symphonies and other works .
label: case obl nsubj root det obj case det amod compound nmod case nmod punct advcl obj case nummod amod nmod cc amod conj punct

text: Although Dvořák was not aware of it , Johannes Brahms was the leading member of the jury and was highly impressed .
label: mark nsubj cop advmod advcl case obl punct nsubj flat cop det amod root case det nmod cc aux advmod conj punct

text: The prize was awarded to Dvořák in 1874 [ a ] and again in 1876 and in 1877 , when Brahms and the prominent critic Eduard Hanslick , also a member of the jury , made themselves known to him .
label: det nsubj aux root case obl case obl punct dep punct cc advmod case conj cc case conj punct advmod nsubj cc det amod conj appos flat punct advmod det appos case det nmod punct advcl obj xcomp case obl punct

text: Brahms recommended Dvořák to his publisher , Simrock , who soon afterward commissioned what became the Slavonic Dances , Op. 46 .
label: nsubj root obj case nmod obl punct appos punct nsubj advmod advmod acl obj acl det amod xcomp punct appos dep punct

text: These were highly praised by the Berlin music critic Louis Ehlert in 1878 , the sheet music ( of the original piano 4 - hands version ) had excellent sales , and Dvořák 's international reputation was launched at last .
label: nsubj aux advmod root case det compound compound obl flat flat case obl punct det compound nsubj punct case det amod compound nummod punct compound nmod punct conj amod obj punct cc nmod case amod nsubj aux conj case obl punct

text: Dvořák 's first piece of a religious nature , his setting of Stabat Mater , was premiered in Prague in 1880 .
label: nmod case amod nsubj case det amod nmod punct nmod appos case nmod flat punct aux root case obl case obl punct

text: It was very successfully performed in London in 1883 , leading to many other performances in the United Kingdom and United States . [ 2 ]
label: nsubj aux advmod advmod root case obl case obl punct advcl case amod amod obl case det amod nmod cc amod conj punct punct dep punct

text: In his career , Dvořák made nine invited visits to England , often conducting performances of his own works .
label: case nmod obl punct nsubj root nummod amod obj case nmod punct advmod advcl obj case nmod amod nmod punct

text: His Seventh Symphony was written for London .
label: nmod amod nsubj aux root case obl punct

text: Visiting Russia in March 1890 , he conducted concerts of his own music in Moscow and Saint Petersburg . [ 3 ]
label: advcl obj case obl nmod punct nsubj root obj case nmod amod nmod case obl cc conj flat punct punct dep punct

text: In 1891 Dvořák was appointed as a professor at the Prague Conservatory .
label: case obl nsubj aux root case det obl case det compound nmod punct

text: In 1890 – 91 , he wrote his Dumky Trio , one of his most successful chamber music pieces .
label: case obl case nmod punct nsubj root nmod compound obj punct appos case nmod advmod amod compound compound nmod punct

text: In 1892 , Dvořák moved to the United States and became the director of the National Conservatory of Music of America in New York City .
label: case obl punct nsubj root case det amod obl cc conj det xcomp case det amod nmod case nmod case nmod case amod compound nmod punct

text: While in the United States , Dvořák wrote his two most successful orchestral works : the Symphony From the New World , which spread his reputation worldwide , [ 4 ] and his Cello Concerto , one of the most highly regarded of all cello concerti .
label: mark case det amod advcl punct nsubj root nmod nummod advmod amod amod obj punct det appos case det amod nmod punct nsubj acl nmod obj advmod punct punct dislocated punct cc nmod compound conj punct appos case det advmod advmod nmod case det compound obl punct

text: He also wrote his most appreciated piece of chamber music , the American String Quartet , during this time .
label: nsubj advmod root nmod advmod amod obj case compound nmod punct det amod compound appos punct case det obl punct

text: But shortfalls in payment of his salary , along with increasing recognition in Europe and an onset of homesickness , led him to leave the United States and return to Bohemia in 1895 .
label: cc nsubj case nmod case nmod nmod punct advmod case amod obl case nmod cc det conj case nmod punct root obj mark xcomp det amod obj cc conj case obl case obl punct

text: All of Dvořák 's nine operas but his first have librettos in Czech and were intended to convey Czech national spirit , as were some of his choral works .
label: nsubj case nmod case nummod nmod case nmod nmod root obj case nmod cc aux conj mark xcomp amod amod obj punct mark advcl nsubj case nmod amod nmod punct

text: By far the most successful of the operas is Rusalka .

text: Among his smaller works , the seventh Humoresque and the song " Songs My Mother Taught Me " are also widely performed and recorded .

text: This year has once again confirmed the importance of the United Nations as the truly indispensable multilateral forum for addressing today ’s global problems .
label: det nsubj aux advmod advmod root det obj case det amod nmod case det advmod amod amod nmod mark acl nmod case amod obj punct

label: det amod nsubj case det nmod case nmod punct amod conj case fixed nmod punct amod conj case det amod nmod cc amod conj case fixed det nmod case det amod compound nmod case nmod amod nmod root amod obj case det amod nmod cc nmod compound conj punct

label: det nsubj case nmod aux root case det obl cc aux cop conj case obl punct

text: Austria welcomes all efforts undertaken by Governments in the region for peaceful and credible change .
label: nsubj root det obj acl case obl case det nmod case amod cc conj nmod punct

text: We encourage the newly empowered authorities to create a constitutional framework based on democracy and human rights , in order to fulfil their mandate for democratic change responsibly and peacefully .
label: nsubj root det advmod amod obj mark xcomp det amod obj acl case obl cc amod conj punct mark fixed mark advcl nmod obj case amod nmod advmod cc conj punct

text: The events in the Arab world notwithstanding , we must continue to focus on the Middle East peace process .
label: det obl case det amod nmod case punct nsubj aux root mark xcomp case det compound compound compound obl punct

text: The Middle East took centre stage this week here at the General Assembly — and rightly so .
label: det compound nsubj root compound obj det obl advmod case det compound obl punct cc advmod conj punct

text: We must build trust and we have to foster the belief among Israelis and Palestinians that a negotiated settlement can be achieved — a sustainable solution based on two States living side by side in a secure and peaceful neighbourhood within mutually recognized borders .
label: nsubj aux root obj cc nsubj conj mark xcomp det obj case nmod cc conj mark det amod nsubj aux aux acl punct det amod dislocated acl case nummod obl acl obl case nmod case det amod cc conj obl case advmod amod obl punct

text: Austria fully supports the Quartet statement .

text: There is no time to lose .

text: Austria welcomes President Al - Nasser ’s choice of theme for this year ’s general debate .

text: We appreciate Qatar ’s strong track record in that regard .
label: nsubj root nmod case amod compound obj case det nmod punct

text: Last year ’s tenth anniversary of the adoption of Security Council resolution 1325 ( 2000 ) on women , peace and security reminded us that the promise of women ’s full and equal participation in all efforts of maintaining peace and security , including in mediation processes , has not yet come true and that we all need to intensify our efforts .

text: In that context , let me also mention an Austrian contribution to international mediation efforts .
label: case det obl punct root obj advmod xcomp det amod obj case amod compound nmod punct

text: By inviting political decision - makers from both Khartoum and Juba to Vienna in recent years , Austria has managed to offer the two sides a platform for discussion .

text: The Sudan and South Sudan have a shared past and must resolve their remaining problems peacefully .
label: det nsubj cc compound conj root det amod obj cc aux conj nmod amod obj advmod punct

text: The United Nations headquarters in Vienna serves as a dynamic hub for the promotion of peace , security and sustainable development .
label: det amod compound nsubj case nmod root case det amod obl case det nmod case nmod punct conj cc amod conj punct

text: Over the past year , the International Anti-Corruption Academy set up its headquarters near Vienna , and the Vienna Centre for Disarmament and Non-Proliferation and an office of the International Peace Institute were established .
label: case det amod obl punct det amod compound nsubj root compound nmod obj case obl punct cc det compound nsubj case nmod cc conj cc det conj case det amod compound nmod aux conj punct

text: Austria fully stands behind the campaign launched by the Secretary - General on Monday to achieve universal access to modern energy services .
label: nsubj advmod root case det obl acl case det obl punct flat case obl mark acl amod obj case amod compound nmod punct

label: nsubj root ccomp det obj case nmod case compound nmod cc det conj case amod nmod case det amod compound nmod case obl punct

text: Austria provides substantial support to the energy and environment efforts undertaken by the United Nations Industrial Development Organization .
label: nsubj root amod obj case det compound cc conj obl acl case det amod compound amod compound obl punct

label: nsubj root mark xcomp det amod obj case det amod amod nmod case nmod punct flat case nmod flat punct

text: On Friday , 28 February , New Zealand recorded its first case of the COVID - 19 coronavirus , becoming the 48th country to have a confirmed case .

text: I can report to the House that they are currently in a stable and improving condition at Auckland Hospital .
label: nsubj aux root case det obl mark nsubj cop advmod case det amod cc conj ccomp case nmod flat punct

text: The good news in this instance is that the individual had limited contact with people upon their return to the country , and their family took all the appropriate measures when presenting at the emergency department .
label: det amod nsubj case det nmod cop mark det nsubj root amod obj case nmod case nmod obl case det nmod punct cc nmod nsubj conj det det amod obj advmod advcl case det compound obl punct

text: As you would expect , our public health service is working hard to contain this first case and limit the risk of any spread of the disease .
label: mark nsubj aux advcl punct nmod amod compound nsubj aux root advmod mark advcl det amod obj cc conj det obj case det nmod case det nmod punct

text: Contact tracing began immediately and has gone to plan .

label: det nummod nsubj nsubj aux acl case det obl case nmod obl case nmod flat aux aux root cc aux aux conj mark compound punct xcomp punct

text: Public health staff will remain in touch with individuals to monitor the situation and give ongoing advice .

text: All but 10 of the remaining passengers on the flight , who are not considered to be close contacts , have also been contacted to provide reassurance and answer any questions they might have ; those 10 that have n't been contacted did not provide accurate contact information .
label: nsubj case nmod case det amod nmod case det nmod punct nsubj aux advmod acl mark cop amod xcomp punct aux advmod aux root mark advcl obj cc conj det obj nsubj aux acl punct det nsubj nsubj aux advmod aux acl aux advmod parataxis amod compound obj punct

text: I 'm advised that as a result of our decisive response , the chance of an outbreak from our first case is low .
label: nsubj aux root mark case det obl case nmod amod nmod punct det nsubj case det nmod case nmod amod nmod cop ccomp punct

text: Internationally , the situation with COVID - 19 continues to develop at pace .
label: advmod punct det nsubj case nmod punct flat root mark xcomp case obl punct

text: However , the Director - General of the World Health Organization said , this morning , containment … is feasible and must remain the top priority for all countries .
label: advmod punct det nsubj punct flat case det compound compound nmod root punct det obl punct nsubj punct cop ccomp cc aux conj det amod xcomp case det nmod punct

text: This is exactly the approach that New Zealand is taking , using three main tools : border controls ; self - isolation ; and good public health practices , including highlighting the importance of basic hygiene .
label: nsubj cop advmod det root obj nsubj flat aux acl punct advcl nummod amod obj punct compound appos punct compound punct conj punct cc amod amod compound conj punct acl ccomp det obj case amod nmod punct

text: At every step , the Government has taken decisions in the interests of health and safety of the wider public , and so far we have been among the best at keeping COVID - 19 at bay .
label: case det obl punct det nsubj aux root obj case det obl case nmod cc conj case det amod nmod punct cc advmod advmod nsubj aux cop case det conj mark advcl obj punct flat case xcomp punct

text: Just yesterday , Cabinet decided to extend for another week the travel restrictions that have been in place for China since 3 February and for Iran since last Friday .
label: advmod obl punct nsubj root mark xcomp case det obl det compound obj nsubj aux aux case acl case obl case obl compound cc case conj case amod orphan punct

text: These restrictions have played a key role in keeping COVID - 19 out of New Zealand for so long and have given us time to better understand the disease and ramp up our preparations .
label: det nsubj aux root det amod obj mark acl obj punct flat case fixed obl flat case advmod obl cc aux conj iobj obj mark advmod acl det obj cc conj compound nmod obj punct

text: Of course , members will be aware that there are outbreaks in other regions as well .
label: advmod fixed punct nsubj aux cop root mark expl ccomp nsubj case amod obl advmod fixed punct

text: So , as a further precaution , we have decided that anyone arriving in New Zealand who has been in northern Italy or South Korea who has been there in the last 14 days will be registered for self - isolation .

text: This is based on an expert assessment of risk .
label: nsubj aux root case det amod obl case nmod punct

text: It recognises that while there are outbreaks in both countries , they also have well - developed health systems and the outbreaks are largely located in specific regions .
label: nsubj root mark mark expl advcl nsubj case det obl punct nsubj advmod ccomp advmod punct amod compound obj cc det nsubj aux advmod conj case amod obl punct

text: We know self - isolation works .
label: nsubj root compound punct nsubj ccomp punct

text: It is a longstanding and successful approach to managing infectious diseases and has proven its worth again in recent weeks .
label: nsubj cop det amod cc conj root mark acl amod obj cc aux conj nmod obj advmod case amod obl punct

text: We have also stepped up the health presence at our airports .
label: nsubj aux advmod root compound det compound obj case nmod nmod punct

text: 2.1 Early Ideas in Atomic Theory
label: dep amod root case amod nmod

text: By the end of this section , you will be able to :
label: case det obl case det nmod punct nsubj aux cop root xcomp punct

text: State the postulates of Dalton ’s atomic theory
label: root det obj case nmod case amod nmod

text: Use postulates of Dalton ’s atomic theory to explain the laws of definite and multiple proportions
label: root obj case nmod case amod nmod mark advcl det obj case amod cc conj nmod

text: The earliest recorded discussion of the basic structure of matter comes from ancient Greek philosophers , the scientists of their day .
label: det amod amod nsubj case det amod nmod case nmod root case amod amod obl punct det appos case nmod nmod punct

text: In the fifth century BC , Leucippus and Democritus argued that all matter was composed of small , finite particles that they called atomos , a term derived from the Greek word for “ indivisible . ”
label: case det amod obl advmod punct nsubj cc conj root mark det nsubj aux ccomp case amod punct amod obl obj nsubj acl xcomp punct det appos acl case det amod obl case punct nmod punct punct

text: They thought of atoms as moving particles that differed in shape and size , and which could join together .
label: nsubj root case obl case amod obl nsubj acl case obl cc conj punct cc nsubj aux conj advmod punct

text: Later , Aristotle and others came to the conclusion that matter consisted of various combinations of the four “ elements ” — fire , earth , air , and water — and could be infinitely divided .
label: advmod punct nsubj cc conj root case det obl mark nsubj acl case amod obl case det nummod punct nmod punct punct appos punct conj punct conj punct cc conj punct cc aux aux advmod conj punct

text: Interestingly , these philosophers thought about atoms and “ elements ” as philosophical concepts , but apparently never considered performing experiments to test their ideas .
label: advmod punct det nsubj root case obl cc punct conj punct case amod obl punct cc advmod advmod conj xcomp obj mark advcl nmod obj punct

text: The Aristotelian view of the composition of matter held sway for over two thousand years , until English schoolteacher John Dalton helped to revolutionize chemistry with his hypothesis that the behavior of matter could be explained using an atomic theory .
label: det amod nsubj case det nmod case nmod root obj case advmod compound nummod obl punct mark amod nsubj flat flat advcl mark xcomp obj case nmod obl mark det nsubj case nmod aux aux acl advcl det amod obj punct

text: First published in 1807 , many of Dalton ’s hypotheses about the microscopic features of matter are still valid in modern atomic theory .
label: advmod acl case obl punct nsubj case nmod case nmod case det amod nmod case nmod cop advmod root case amod amod obl punct

text: Here are the postulates of Dalton ’s atomic theory .
label: root cop det nsubj case nmod case amod nmod punct

text: 1. Matter is composed of exceedingly small particles called atoms .
label: dep nsubj aux root case advmod amod obl acl xcomp punct

text: An atom is the smallest unit of an element that can participate in a chemical change .
label: det nsubj cop det amod root case det nmod nsubj aux acl case det amod obl punct

text: 2. An element consists of only one type of atom , which has a mass that is characteristic of the element and is the same for all atoms of that element ( Figure 2.2 ) .
label: dep det nsubj root case advmod nummod obl case nmod punct nsubj acl det obj nsubj cop acl case det obl cc cop det conj case det obl case det nmod punct parataxis dep punct punct

text: A macroscopic sample of an element contains an incredibly large number of atoms , all of which have identical chemical properties .
label: det amod nsubj case det nmod root det advmod amod obj case nmod punct nsubj case nmod acl amod amod obj punct

text: Figure 2.2
label: root dep

text: A pre-1982 copper penny ( left ) contains approximately 3 ×× 10 22 copper atoms ( several dozen are represented as brown spheres at the right ) , each of which has the same chemical properties .
label: det amod compound nsubj punct parataxis punct root advmod nummod compound compound compound compound obj punct amod nsubj aux parataxis case amod obl case det obl punct punct nsubj case nmod acl det amod amod obj punct

text: ( credit : modification of work by “ slgckgc ” / Flickr )
label: punct root punct dep case nmod case punct nmod punct punct list punct

text: 3. Atoms of one element differ in properties from atoms of all other elements .
label: dep nsubj case nummod nmod root case obl case obl case det amod nmod punct

text: 4. A compound consists of atoms of two or more elements combined in a small , whole - number ratio .
label: dep det nsubj root case obl case nummod cc conj nmod acl case det amod punct amod punct compound obl punct

text: In a given compound , the numbers of atoms of each of its elements are always present in the same ratio ( Figure 2.3 ) .
label: case det amod obl punct det nsubj case nmod case nmod case nmod nmod cop advmod root case det amod obl punct parataxis dep punct punct

text: Figure 2.3
label: root dep

text: Copper(II) oxide , a powdery , black compound , results from the combination of two types of atoms — copper ( brown spheres ) and oxygen ( red spheres ) — in a 1 : 1 ratio .
label: compound nsubj punct det amod punct amod appos punct root case det obl case nummod nmod case nmod punct appos punct amod parataxis punct cc conj punct amod parataxis punct punct case det compound case nmod nmod punct

text: ( credit : modification of work by “ Chemicalinterest ” / Wikimedia Commons )
label: punct root punct dep case nmod case punct nmod punct cc conj flat punct

text: 5. Atoms are neither created nor destroyed during a chemical change , but are instead rearranged to yield substances that are different from those present before the change ( Figure 2.4 ) .
label: dep nsubj aux cc root cc conj case det amod obl punct cc aux advmod conj mark advcl obj nsubj cop acl case obl acl case det obl punct parataxis dep punct punct

text: Figure 2.4
label: root dep

text: How to Grow Beavertail Cactus
label: root mark acl compound obj

text: The Beavertail Cactus ( Opunitia basilares ) , found primarily in the Mojave Desert and northwest Mexico ; can grow to be about 24 inches ( 60 cm ) high ; has pads that look like beavertails ; and yields red or purple flowers from spring to early summer .

text: Growing Beavertail can be done at any time of year by scattering seeds in a shady bed or , for faster results , planting cuttings in a mix of soil and sand and ensuring that they have a bit of water and plenty of sun .

text: Method 1 of 2 : From Seeds
label: root dep case nmod punct case appos

text: Purchase Beavertail cactus seeds .
label: root compound compound obj punct

text: These can be bought at garden centers or purchased online .
label: nsubj aux aux root case compound obl cc conj advmod punct

text: Scatter the seeds .
label: root det obj punct

text: In a shady garden bed , simply scatter the seeds on the soil .
label: case det amod compound obl punct advmod root det obj case det obl punct

text: There 's no need to cover them , unless you want to use netting to keep the birds off .
label: expl root det nsubj mark acl obj punct mark nsubj advcl mark xcomp obj mark advcl det obj compound punct

text: Keep the soil moist until the seeds germinate .
label: root det obj xcomp mark det nsubj advcl punct

text: Make sure that the garden bed is in the shade .
label: root xcomp mark det compound nsubj cop case det ccomp punct

text: Beavertail cacti seeds need shade to grow , whereas cuttings need plenty of direct sunlight .
label: compound compound nsubj root obj mark advcl punct mark nsubj advcl obj case amod nmod punct

text: Be aware that growing Beavertail cactus from seeds takes much longer than growing one from a cutting .
label: cop root mark csubj compound obj case obl ccomp advmod advmod mark advcl obj case det obl punct

text: It can take as long as 4 to 4 years before you get flowers .
label: nsubj aux root advmod advmod case nummod case nmod obl mark nsubj advcl obj punct

text: Method 2 of 2 : From Cuttings
label: root dep case nmod punct case appos

text: Obtain Beavertail cuttings .
label: root compound obj punct

text: You can purchase them online or at a local garden center .
label: nsubj aux root obj advmod cc case det amod compound conj punct

text: If you already own a Beavertail cactus , you can make your own cuttings .
label: mark nsubj advmod advcl det compound obj punct nsubj aux root nmod amod obj punct

text: To do this , choose pads ( the flat , oval - shaped sections that make up a cactus ) that are 6 months old or older and cut them at the base .
label: mark advcl obj punct root obj punct det amod punct amod punct amod appos nsubj acl compound det obj punct nsubj cop nummod obl acl cc conj cc conj obj case det obl punct

text: In order to form a callous and prevent rot , cure the cuttings by sitting the pad upright in a dry , dark place for 10 to 14 days .
label: mark fixed mark advcl det obj cc conj obj punct root det obj mark advcl det obj xcomp case det amod punct amod obl case nummod case nmod obl punct

text: Plant the cuttings .
label: root det obj punct

text: Prepare a potting mix that is equal parts soil and rough pumice or sand and fill the appropriate number of pots with it .
label: root det compound obj nsubj cop amod nmod acl cc amod conj cc conj cc conj det amod obj case nmod case obl punct

text: Make sure there are holes in the center of the base of each pot to allow for good drainage .
label: root xcomp expl ccomp nsubj case det obl case det nmod case det nmod mark advcl case amod obl punct

text: Set the cuttings upright in the potting mix about an inch ( 2.5 cm. ) deep .
label: root det obj xcomp case det compound obl advmod det obl punct nummod appos punct obl punct

text: If you plant the cuttings too deep , they might rot .
label: mark nsubj advcl det obj advmod advmod punct nsubj aux root punct

text: Put some rocks around the pad to anchor it in place .
label: root det obj case det obl mark advcl obj case obl punct

text: Choose a spot for your Beavertail cactus cuttings .
label: root det obj case nmod compound compound nmod punct

text: If you live in an area with strong summer sun , position the cuttings so that the broad sides of the cuttings face east and west while the slim sides face north and south .
label: mark nsubj advcl case det obl case amod compound nmod punct root det obj mark fixed det amod nsubj case det nmod advcl advmod cc conj mark det amod nsubj advcl advmod cc conj punct

text: This will prevent the cuttings from burning during the hottest part of the day .
label: nsubj aux root det obj mark advcl case det amod obl case det nmod punct

text: Make sure the spot is sheltered from any cold winter winds .
label: root xcomp det nsubj aux ccomp case det amod compound obl punct

text: Wait for a month .
label: root case det obl punct

text: Do not water the cutting for the first month .
label: aux advmod root det obj case det amod nmod punct

text: The moisture in the pad will provide enough nutrients for roots to grow .
label: det nsubj case det nmod aux root amod obj mark nsubj mark acl punct

text: Too much water might cause rot .
label: advmod amod nsubj aux root obj punct

text: After 1 month , roots will have sprouted and you can water the cutting for the first time .

text: Always let the soil dry before you water the cuttings .

text: How to Get Rid of Mice Naturally

text: Having mice in your home is both a nuisance and a health hazard .

text: They can cause property damage , create a mess , and produce unpleasant smells .

text: Method 1 Discouraging Mice Naturally

text: Keep your home clean .

text: Many times mice are drawn into homes on the search for food .

text: If there is nothing to eat , mice will be less likely to stay .

text: Keep all food stored properly in airtight containers or in places that are safe from mouse attack . [ 1 ]
label: root det obj xcomp advmod case amod obl cc case conj nsubj cop acl case compound obl punct punct dep punct

text: Apply peppermint oil .

text: Peppermint oil is a natural deterrent .

text: The smell is simply too intense for rodents and they will not try to go near it .
label: det nsubj cop advmod advmod root case obl cc nsubj aux advmod conj mark xcomp case obl punct

text: It also helps to mask the scent of any tasty morsels that have been missed when cleaning .

text: It also gives the house a lovely smell , and is not toxic , unlike many synthetic chemical treatments .

text: You can get peppermint oil in most health food stores and even some major grocery stores . [ 2 ]

text: Place a drop or two on a cotton ball .

text: Place the cotton balls in areas where mice are likely to enter your house , by doorways , or heat vents , etc.
label: root det compound obj case obl advmod nsubj cop advcl mark xcomp nmod obj punct case obl punct cc compound conj punct conj

text: Use dried snake feces .

text: Visit a local reptile center , zoo , or pet store and ask for some dried snake poo .

text: You can also sometimes find someone who owns a pet snake .

text: Place near entrances and in places where mice seem to go .

text: This will keep mice away . [ 3 ]
